Thomas Elliot's middle name was Stewart!

730
00:54:31,633 --> 00:54:33,426
Once again.

731
00:54:33,427 --> 00:54:35,512
The arcuate fasciculus,
Wernicke's area...

732
00:54:44,438 --> 00:54:46,523
So this is where it all happens, is it?

733
00:54:47,024 --> 00:54:49,151
Spencer? What are you doing here?

734
00:54:49,234 --> 00:54:52,111
I thought I'd pay you a
visit. You don't mind, do you?

735
00:54:52,613 --> 00:54:54,031
No.

736
00:54:57,618 --> 00:55:00,746
Really good to see you, Spence,
just a bit of a surprise, that's all.

737
00:55:00,829 --> 00:55:01,913
Who let you in, anyway?

738
00:55:02,039 --> 00:55:04,541
Some wanker in a velvet waistcoat.

739
00:55:05,751 --> 00:55:07,544
You were nice to him,
though, weren't you?

740
00:55:07,628 --> 00:55:09,129
I don't know. Should I have been?

741
00:55:10,422 --> 00:55:12,715
It's just, I do have to live
with him, and I just asked?

742
00:55:12,841 --> 00:55:14,843
Yeah? Are you writing poetry?

743
00:55:14,927 --> 00:55:18,430
No. Give me that! Give me that!

744
00:55:20,849 --> 00:55:22,642
- Give me that.
- Who's Alice anyway?

745
00:55:23,435 --> 00:55:24,727
With the big bosoms?

746
00:55:24,853 --> 00:55:26,145
You're not serious?

747
00:55:27,147 --> 00:55:29,732
You are serious. Bloody
hell, Spencer. What now?

748
00:55:29,816 --> 00:55:32,026
I'm being prosecuted for
fiddling me unemployment benefit.

749
00:55:32,152 --> 00:55:33,236
What's gonna happen?

750
00:55:33,237 --> 00:55:35,530
I don't know. Depends
on the judge, I suppose.

751
00:55:36,448 --> 00:55:39,617
But you still got the arcade job, right?

752
00:55:39,743 --> 00:55:43,037
Not as such, no. They sort of
found me with my hand in the till.

753
00:55:43,121 --> 00:55:44,539
What do they think you took?

754
00:55:44,623 --> 00:55:46,750
- Couple of hundred.
- How much did you take?

755
00:55:46,833 --> 00:55:48,626
Yeah, couple of hundred
sounds about right.

756
00:55:48,752 --> 00:55:49,919
Spencer.

757
00:55:50,045 --> 00:55:52,922
You're a socialist. I thought you
approved of the redistribution of wealth.

758
00:55:53,048 --> 00:55:56,718
By acquiring the means of
production. Not by just nicking stuff.

759
00:55:56,843 --> 00:55:59,136
Can we talk about something else?

760
00:55:59,221 --> 00:56:01,932
I came here to get away from all that.
Have a bit of a laugh, bit of fun, yeah.

761
00:56:02,015 --> 00:56:04,934
Okay. Yeah, we can do that.

762
00:56:07,229 --> 00:56:09,814
- Is she gonna be there?
- Who?

763
00:56:10,023 --> 00:56:14,235
You know, the posh one.
The one in the poems.

764
00:56:14,236 --> 00:56:17,447
Alice? I hope so. Be
nice, though, won't you?

765
00:56:17,531 --> 00:56:20,534
Who, me? I'm always nice.

766
00:56:20,617 --> 00:56:23,244
This hand and a bucket of water...

767
00:56:23,328 --> 00:56:25,830
Look, let's move on.

